    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 9,
        "summary": "Isaiah speaks about the Messiah\u2014The people in darkness will see a great Light\u2014Unto us a Child is born\u2014He will be the Prince of Peace and reign on David's throne\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 19.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless the dimness shall not be such as was in her vexation, when at the first he lightly afflicted the land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali, and afterward did more grievously afflict her by the way of the sea, beyond Jordan, in Galilee of the nations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 19:1 (1\u201321).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rabbinical commentators relate this to the attacks by Assyria under Tiglath-pileser and Sargon\u00a0\u2161.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 4:15 (14\u201316).",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 194,
                        "end": 200
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The people that walked in darkness have seen a great light: they that dwell in the land of the shadow of death, upon them hath the light shined.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The \u201cdimness\u201d and \u201cdarkness\u201d were apostasy and captivity (Isa. 8:20\u201322); the \u201cgreat light\u201d is Christ (Isa. 9:6\u20137). TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Light of the World; Light [noun].",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou hast multiplied the nation, and not increased the joy: they joy before thee according to the joy in harvest, and as men rejoice when they divide the spoil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 26:15.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 2:9.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:162.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For thou hast broken the yoke of his burden, and the staff of his shoulder, the rod of his oppressor, as in the day of Midian.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 10:27 (24\u201327).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 14:5.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0was broken in the day of Midian.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 7:23 (19\u201323); Isa. 10:26.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 873
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For every battle of the warrior is with confused noise, and garments rolled in blood; but this shall be with burning and fuel of fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0When the whole battle \u2026 was with confused noise, and \u2026 blood.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "This \u201cburning\u201d is to be the cleansing of the earth by fire prior to the setting up of the messianic kingdom. 3\u00a0Ne. 25:1; D&C 64:23 (23\u201324); JS\u2014H 1:37.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 116
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For unto us a child is born, unto us a son is given: and the government shall be upon his shoulder: and his name shall be called Wonderful, Counsellor, The mighty God, The everlasting Father, The Prince of Peace.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Prophecies about.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Manifestations of; Jesus Christ, Birth of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments; Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Millennial Reign; Jesus Christ, Mission of.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Counselor.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 150
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Power of.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 162
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 7:27 (26\u201327).",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 166
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Immortality.",
                        "start": 172,
                        "end": 183
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace; Peace of God.",
                        "start": 206,
                        "end": 211
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p6",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Of the increase of his government and peace there shall be no end, upon the throne of David, and upon his kingdom, to order it, and to establish it with judgment and with justice from henceforth even for ever. The zeal of the Lord of hosts will perform this.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments; Kingdom of God, on Earth.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 1:33 (32\u201333).",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Davidic Descent of.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Justice of; Justice.",
                        "start": 171,
                        "end": 178
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zeal.",
                        "start": 214,
                        "end": 218
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord sent a word into Jacob, and it hath lighted upon Israel.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0The prophetic message that follows (vv.\u00a08\u201321) was a warning to the northern ten tribes, called Israel.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And all the people shall know, even Ephraim and the inhabitant of Samaria, that say in the pride and stoutness of heart,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:28 (28\u201329).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The bricks are fallen down, but we will build with hewn stones: the sycomores are cut down, but we will change them into cedars.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the Lord shall set up the adversaries of Rezin against him, and join his enemies together;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 7:1.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Syrians before, and the Philistines behind; and they shall devour Israel with open mouth. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0on the east.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0on the west.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 4:8.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0In spite of all, the Lord is available if they will turn to Him (also vv.\u00a017, 21).",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 144
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 150,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the people turneth not unto him that smiteth them, neither do they seek the Lord of hosts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 7:10.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the Lord will cut off from Israel head and tail, branch and rush, in one day.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The ancient and honourable, he is the head; and the prophet that teacheth lies, he is the tail.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0elder and man of rank. 2\u00a0Ne. 19:15.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Prophets.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the leaders of this people cause them to err; and they that are led of them are destroyed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leadership.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:31.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the Lord shall have no joy in their young men, neither shall have mercy on their fatherless and widows: for every one is an hypocrite and an evildoer, and every mouth speaketh folly. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 143
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:25.",
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 185
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 130
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 249,
                        "end": 251
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For wickedness burneth as the fire: it shall devour the briers and thorns, and shall kindle in the thickets of the forest, and they shall mount up like the lifting up of smoke.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 10:17.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 10:34.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 151
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Through the wrath of the Lord of hosts is the land darkened, and the people shall be as the fuel of the fire: no man shall spare his brother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 9:2; JS\u2014M 1:30.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 128
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 38:21; Micah 7:2 (2, 6).",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 874
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall snatch on the right hand, and be hungry; and he shall eat on the left hand, and they shall not be satisfied: they shall eat every man the flesh of his own arm:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hag. 1:6.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 19:9.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Manasseh, Ephraim; and Ephraim, Manasseh: and they together shall be against Judah. For all this his anger is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
